sk for more until he stopped at seven readings.\u201d Ibn Shihab said, \u201cIt reached\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":32670,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/07\/05\/seven-ahruf-do-not-argue\/","url_meta":{"origin":31900,"position":1},"title":"Hadith Ahruf: Quran revealed in seven readings, do not argue it","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 5, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Juhaym reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThe Quran is recited in seven ways. Do not argue over the Quran, for arguing over the Quran is an act of unbelief.\u201d Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad 17199 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Suyuti \u0639\u0646 \u0623\u0628\u064a \u062c\u064f\u0647\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0645\u064d \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0627\u0644\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0651\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":35076,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/01\/26\/allah-commands-forgiveness\/","url_meta":{"origin":31900,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Pardon: Allah commands the Prophet to forgive bad manners","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 26, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Sufyan ibn \u2018Uyaynah reported: When the verse was revealed, \u201cHold to forgiveness, enjoin what is good, and turn away from the ignorant,\u201d (7:199), the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cO Gabriel, what is this?\u201d Gabriel said, \u201cI do not know until I ask the All-Knowing.\u201d\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":27515,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/04\/11\/ramadan-jibreel-quran-twice\/","url_meta":{"origin":31900,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Ramadan: Gabriel comes to review the Quran twice","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 11, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Fatimah reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cGabriel would come to me to revise the Quran once every year. This year he revised with me twice. I do not think it means anything but that my term will come to an end. Verily, you will be\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":35863,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/04\/27\/fatihah-baqarah-descend\/","url_meta":{"origin":31900,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Quran: Al-Fatihah and al-Baqarah descend from heaven","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 27, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abbas reported: While the Angel Gabriel was sitting with the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, he heard a creaking noise above him. Gabriel raised his head and he said, \u201cThis is a door of heaven that has been opened today and it has never been opened before\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":6609,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/09\/18\/punishment-jahannam-backbiting\/","url_meta":{"origin":31900,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Backbiting: Horrific punishment in Hellfire","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 18, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhen I was taken on my night journey, I passed by people who had metal hooks in their hands, and they were clawing at their faces and chests. I said: Who are these, O Gabriel?\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/31900","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=31900"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/31900\/revisions"}],"wp:attachmen